# Pactkeeper conventions

Read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) for full architecture. These are the
non-negotiables enforced every turn.

## Units

`TILE = TILE_PX * SCALE = 32` screen px per tile. Three coordinate systems —
never mix them in one expression:

- **Tile coords** `(tx, ty)`: integers, `0..GRID_W-1`. Used by `PATH`,
  placement, `PATH_TILES`.
- **Screen pixels** `(x, y)`: floats. Used by `pos`, mouse, all `ctx.draw*`.
- **Logical sprite pixels** `0..16`: sprite source data. Multiply by `SCALE`.

Convert at the boundary: `Math.floor(mx / TILE)` for px → tile,
`tx * TILE + TILE / 2` for tile → centered px.

## Registries (single source of truth)

Game content **must** be added to its registry, not hard-coded:

| Content | Registry | File |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Tower stats | `TOWER_DEFS` | `src/config.ts` |
| Enemy stats | `ENEMY_DEFS` | `src/config.ts` |
| Hero stats | `HEROES` | `src/heroes.ts` |
| Pacts | `PACTS` | `src/modifiers.ts` |
| Waves | `WAVES` | `src/waves.ts` |
| Sprites | `SPRITES_16` | `src/sprites.ts` |
| Sigils | `SIGILS` | `src/sigils.ts` |

If you find yourself writing `if (kind === "arrow") ...` outside a registry,
extend the registry instead.

## Pairing rules — when you change X, also change Y

`scripts/doc-check.ts` enforces most of these at build time. Failing to do
the paired edit will fail `npm run build`.

| Edited | Also touch | Why |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `TOWER_DEFS` (add a kind) | `TOWER_KINDS` in `hud.ts`, `SPRITES_16` (add `<kind>Tower`), `docs/recipes.md` | HUD shows the card; sprite renders it |
| `ENEMY_DEFS` (add a kind) | `SPRITES_16`, `ENEMY_SCORE` in `score.ts`, `BREACH_LIFE_COST` in `game.ts` (if breach > 1 life), `docs/recipes.md` | Otherwise enemy renders blank, scoring crashes, or breach is silent |
| Boss kind (any of `hollow_warden` / `brood_mother` / `cinder_lich`) | `ENEMY_DEFS` row, `BOSS_PHASE2_SPEED_MULT`, `BOSS_PHASE2_TINT` (all `config.ts`), `SPRITES_16` + palette + `paletteFor`, `LEVELS[id].boss` + `bossName` in `levels.ts` | Doc-check enforces the pairing — missing any field skips 2× render, enrage, or halo |
| `HEROES` (add a kind) | `SPRITES_16` (add `<kind>Hero`), `HERO_KINDS` order in `heroes.ts`, `docs/recipes.md`, optional new `PactkeeperSFXInstance` method | Otherwise picker missing card, sprite missing, doc-check fails |
| `PACTS` (add a pact) | `SIGILS` in `sigils.ts` (only if new sigil id) | Pact card needs its sigil |
| Adapted-copy `apply()` | `AGENTS.md` "Known anomalies" section | Document the approximation so it's not lost |
| `PATH` | `PROPS` in `map.ts` (move trees off the new path) | Defensive skip exists but visuals look wrong |
| New `.ts` file in `src/` | `AGENTS.md` repo-layout table | doc-check fails if missing |

## No magic numbers in `game.ts`

Tunables live in `config.ts`. Layout constants stay at the top of the file
that uses them (`hud.ts`, `screens.ts`).

## Effects flow through arguments, not globals

Sim primitives never read `Game` state. They take `PactEffects` multipliers as
parameters:

```typescript
// ✅ The contract
spawnEnemy(kind, hpMult, speedMult, bountyMult)
updateTower(t, dt, enemies, damageMult, rangeMult, nowSec, outProjectiles)
```

## Update vs render

`updateX(...)` mutates state. `drawX(...)` reads state and calls `ctx.draw*`.
Never the other way around.

## Definition of done

Before considering a change complete:

1. `npm run build` passes (= `tsc` + doc-check + vite build)
2. If you touched a registry, you ran the pairing rules above
3. If you added a `src/` file, it's in `AGENTS.md` repo layout
4. If you wrote `Adapted copy:` anywhere, it's reflected in `AGENTS.md`
